Quality

qplot(wdf$quality) +
  xlab('quality')
## stat_bin: binwidth defaulted to range/30. Use 'binwidth = x' to adjust this.

It is better to convert qulaity variable to categorical variable, because its values are always integers.

wdf$quality <- factor(wdf$quality)
qplot(wdf$quality) +  xlab('quality')

summary(wdf$quality)
##   3   4   5   6   7   8 
##  10  53 681 638 199  18

Quality has 6 scores, from 3 to 6. Most of all have 5 or 6.

Univariate Analysis

Bivariate Plots Section

pairs(~fixed.acidity + volatile.acidity + citric.acid + residual.sugar +
        chlorides + free.sulfur.dioxide + total.sulfur.dioxide + 
        density + pH + sulphates + alcohol + quality, 
      data = wdf, main = "Example")
